1
00:00:05,040 --> 00:00:08,050
(The following content may not
be suitable for viewers under 15.)

2
00:00:08,050 --> 00:00:09,580
(Viewer discretion is advised.)

3
00:00:46,890 --> 00:00:50,890
(All characters, places, companies,)

4
00:00:50,890 --> 00:00:54,289
(and incidents in this
drama are fictitious.)

5
00:00:55,060 --> 00:00:58,030
The first thing I realized after
reading Jin Jae Gyu's memories...

6
00:00:58,329 --> 00:01:00,829
is that out of the 57 years
of his life,

7
00:01:01,170 --> 00:01:02,600
he was happy...

8
00:01:02,729 --> 00:01:05,200
for merely a couple of years.

9
00:01:07,569 --> 00:01:09,340
To him, true happiness...

10
00:01:10,379 --> 00:01:11,939
was experienced
only during his childhood.

11
00:01:31,900 --> 00:01:33,829
Why do you have to kill goats?

12
00:01:34,329 --> 00:01:35,700
In order to save a life.

13
00:01:37,540 --> 00:01:39,370
Whose life are you trying to save
by killing it?

14
00:01:39,670 --> 00:01:42,010
I'm sacrificing it
to save a human's life.

15
00:01:43,170 --> 00:01:46,849
Is a human's life more precious
than an animal's?

16
00:01:48,549 --> 00:01:52,049
I don't know much about it,

17
00:01:52,680 --> 00:01:55,489
but these animals
have been virtuous...

18
00:01:56,189 --> 00:01:58,090
and will go to a nice place.

19
00:01:58,689 --> 00:01:59,760
Where?

20
00:02:00,189 --> 00:02:01,390
Somewhere nice.

21
00:02:02,230 --> 00:02:03,959
Let's go home...

22
00:02:04,859 --> 00:02:07,099
and wish the goat well.

23
00:02:24,919 --> 00:02:28,050
Don't come near the shrine,
or else, you'll bring in bad luck.

24
00:02:56,310 --> 00:02:57,379
Let's go.

25
00:03:14,599 --> 00:03:15,629
Here.

26
00:03:37,759 --> 00:03:40,689
I'm going to save lives like you do.

27
00:03:42,759 --> 00:03:43,960
Don't do that.

28
00:03:44,599 --> 00:03:46,330
I've been praying
to the spirits constantly...

29
00:03:46,330 --> 00:03:48,430
so that they wouldn't visit you.

30
00:03:48,669 --> 00:03:50,370
Don't you know?

31
00:03:51,139 --> 00:03:53,099
I'm not going to become a shaman.

32
00:03:54,310 --> 00:03:57,080
I'm going to become
a judge or a prosecutor.

33
00:04:03,349 --> 00:04:05,120
Is that okay?

34
00:04:07,990 --> 00:04:09,419
Of course.

35
00:04:24,740 --> 00:04:28,540
However, her wish never came true.

36
00:04:31,680 --> 00:04:34,980
Hwang Pil Sun.
You will die a horrible death.

37
00:04:35,410 --> 00:04:37,350
- When she died,
- Mom!

38
00:04:37,980 --> 00:04:40,420
- the spirits that possessed her...
- Mom!

39
00:04:41,389 --> 00:04:42,689
went to him.

40
00:04:43,019 --> 00:04:44,060
Is anyone in?

41
00:04:49,660 --> 00:04:51,029
Anyone?

42
00:04:56,730 --> 00:04:57,839
My goodness!

43
00:05:14,750 --> 00:05:16,589
He prayed to the spirits
to save his mom,

44
00:05:17,019 --> 00:05:18,189
but it was of no use.

45
00:05:19,319 --> 00:05:21,790
And that was the end
of his happiness.

46
00:05:24,699 --> 00:05:29,399
(15 years later, 1986)

47
00:05:46,250 --> 00:05:49,189
- What are you doing?
- He wants to speak with you.

48
00:05:54,430 --> 00:05:55,459
What?

49
00:06:02,470 --> 00:06:05,100
Come on! I told you
I don't want to get married!

50
00:06:05,100 --> 00:06:07,470
His father is the chief justice,
and he's an elite prosecutor.

51
00:06:07,470 --> 00:06:09,139
Isn't that nice?

52
00:06:14,980 --> 00:06:16,009
What is going on?

53
00:06:29,889 --> 00:06:30,959
My goodness!

54
00:06:33,699 --> 00:06:35,629
- It's me.
- Who are you?

55
00:06:35,629 --> 00:06:36,730
Be quiet.

56
00:06:37,139 --> 00:06:38,569
What do you want?

57
00:06:39,769 --> 00:06:40,910
I guess you forgot about me.

58
00:06:41,939 --> 00:06:44,079
I'm the son of the shaman
you poisoned to death.

59
00:06:45,410 --> 00:06:46,480
That...

60
00:06:47,610 --> 00:06:49,310
That wench?

61
00:06:50,250 --> 00:06:52,449
Thanks to that hospital director
you bribed,

62
00:06:52,649 --> 00:06:54,720
I rotted in a cell
for the past 15 years.

63
00:06:55,889 --> 00:06:57,990
I was locked up since I was eight.

64
00:06:57,990 --> 00:06:59,519
I'm sorry, ma'am.

65
00:07:00,589 --> 00:07:02,160
He threatened me with a gun.

66
00:07:02,689 --> 00:07:04,699
- I had no choice.
- Shut it!

67
00:07:06,259 --> 00:07:09,930
- There must be a misunderstanding.
- The gunshot was loud.

68
00:07:12,470 --> 00:07:14,509
It was much louder
than I had imagined.

69
00:07:20,879 --> 00:07:22,279
It's a pity
there's only one bullet left.

70
00:07:43,430 --> 00:07:44,699
I want to live.

71
00:07:47,240 --> 00:07:48,939
I want to forget everything
and live an ordinary life.

72
00:07:49,939 --> 00:07:51,040
Let me go...

73
00:07:52,240 --> 00:07:54,079
or just kill me.

74
00:08:25,639 --> 00:08:26,740
Pil Sun!

75
00:08:27,680 --> 00:08:28,779
You...

76
00:08:29,779 --> 00:08:30,980
What are you...

77
00:08:36,090 --> 00:08:37,190
Father.

78
00:08:39,419 --> 00:08:40,559
What did you say?

79
00:08:45,600 --> 00:08:46,730
Father.

80
00:09:05,350 --> 00:09:06,549
What have you done?

81
00:09:23,769 --> 00:09:24,940
I found out way too late...

82
00:09:26,039 --> 00:09:28,840
why the Eraser was so bent...

83
00:09:28,840 --> 00:09:30,309
on making Jin Jae Gyu side with him.

84
00:09:32,940 --> 00:09:34,750
It was because
they had a common enemy.

85
00:09:36,250 --> 00:09:37,950
She was the root of every evil deed.

86
00:09:39,179 --> 00:09:40,320
Hwang Pil Sun.

87
00:10:08,850 --> 00:10:09,909
You guys...

88
00:10:11,879 --> 00:10:13,019
are in huge trouble.

89
00:10:13,080 --> 00:10:14,320
Watch what you say.

90
00:10:16,850 --> 00:10:20,190
Are you aware
that the Eraser is after you?

91
00:10:21,360 --> 00:10:22,460
Don't show them all of your cards.

92
00:10:25,059 --> 00:10:26,399
What do you mean?

93
00:10:26,399 --> 00:10:27,870
What do you think?

94
00:10:28,429 --> 00:10:30,669
This is all happening
thanks to someone...

95
00:10:30,669 --> 00:10:32,870
who committed murder
after getting high.

96
00:10:34,509 --> 00:10:37,710
And his mother
fabricated a suicide note...

97
00:10:37,710 --> 00:10:39,440
and made the rest of his family die.

98
00:10:40,639 --> 00:10:42,950
- Don't be ridiculous.
- This is new.

99
00:10:44,250 --> 00:10:45,450
You're going to feign ignorance?

100
00:10:46,350 --> 00:10:47,490
My goodness.

101
00:10:50,389 --> 00:10:54,029
What I mean is, you're the first one
to raise their voice at me.

102
00:10:55,559 --> 00:10:57,830
You'll be experiencing
many new things in the future.

103
00:10:57,830 --> 00:10:59,330
At the very least,
you'll be behind bars.

104
00:10:59,460 --> 00:11:02,129
In the worst-case scenario,
the Eraser will kill you.

105
00:11:02,269 --> 00:11:04,169
- Shut it.
- Be quiet.

106
00:11:06,799 --> 00:11:08,039
Let me make this clear.

107
00:11:08,909 --> 00:11:12,240
This murderer called the Eraser...

108
00:11:12,240 --> 00:11:14,779
is ultimately after
him and me?

109
00:11:15,350 --> 00:11:18,279
And that's why he abducted
my daughter-in-law?

110
00:11:18,720 --> 00:11:20,080
You nailed it, lady.

111
00:11:20,580 --> 00:11:21,889
She's a chairwoman.

112
00:11:24,620 --> 00:11:27,120
Let's say you're right.

113
00:11:27,360 --> 00:11:30,090
But why would he bring up something
from 20 years ago?

114
00:11:30,090 --> 00:11:32,529
How would I know?
I'm not the psychopath.

115
00:11:32,960 --> 00:11:34,529
He's getting rid
of those under you...

116
00:11:34,899 --> 00:11:36,970
so that you'll be trembling in fear.

117
00:11:38,169 --> 00:11:39,240
Fear?

118
00:11:40,500 --> 00:11:42,440
You know nothing about me, then.

119
00:11:43,610 --> 00:11:45,580
He's harming
their innocent family members,

120
00:11:45,580 --> 00:11:46,840
just like how he abducted Ms. Eun.

121
00:11:48,049 --> 00:11:50,820
Don't be ridiculous.
It's all because of him.

122
00:11:52,179 --> 00:11:54,049
It's true
that the Eraser and I are enemies.

123
00:11:54,350 --> 00:11:56,289
We're dying to kill each other.

124
00:11:57,190 --> 00:11:58,759
Would you like me to be honest?

125
00:11:59,419 --> 00:12:02,330
Up until recently,
I couldn't understand...

126
00:12:02,330 --> 00:12:04,500
why the Eraser did what he did.

127
00:12:04,500 --> 00:12:07,399
But I'm starting to get it now.

128
00:12:07,629 --> 00:12:08,769
I especially understand...

129
00:12:09,799 --> 00:12:11,570
his hatred toward you.

130
00:12:16,669 --> 00:12:18,940
I saw what you did to Jin Jae Gyu.

131
00:12:20,740 --> 00:12:23,309
Look. Explain it
so I can understand.

132
00:12:23,309 --> 00:12:24,779
Do you want me to be
even more honest?

133
00:12:25,320 --> 00:12:27,620
I don't care about your fates.

134
00:12:27,720 --> 00:12:29,389
I only want to save...

135
00:12:29,720 --> 00:12:31,559
the innocent Ms. Eun.

136
00:12:32,620 --> 00:12:34,690
I don't expect you to feel sorry,

137
00:12:35,159 --> 00:12:38,159
but come clean if you want
to save her and her baby.

138
00:12:38,559 --> 00:12:39,860
Come clean about what happened...

139
00:12:40,700 --> 00:12:42,629
to Moon Yong Dae 20 years ago.

140
00:12:46,570 --> 00:12:48,169
I'm only interested in protecting...

141
00:12:49,440 --> 00:12:52,139
my family and my son's honor.

142
00:12:54,110 --> 00:12:55,110
His honor?

143
00:12:55,309 --> 00:12:57,519
Is that more important
than your daughter-in-law's life?

144
00:13:01,419 --> 00:13:03,850
Those who don't have
any honor to protect...

145
00:13:04,419 --> 00:13:05,820
won't understand me.

146
00:13:07,889 --> 00:13:10,330
If anyone taints...

147
00:13:10,330 --> 00:13:11,899
my son's reputation,

148
00:13:14,269 --> 00:13:17,500
you will pay for it
no matter who you are.

149
00:13:20,269 --> 00:13:21,669
You obviously don't know who I am.

150
00:13:26,740 --> 00:13:27,850
Hand them over to the prosecution.

151
00:13:31,750 --> 00:13:32,919
What is this?

152
00:13:33,080 --> 00:13:35,649
You assaulted me first,
and now, you're leaving? Seriously?

153
00:13:44,929 --> 00:13:48,700
(Episode 14: Two Layers of Evil)

154
00:13:54,740 --> 00:13:55,970
Darn it.

155
00:14:03,279 --> 00:14:05,720
Move! I said, move!

156
00:14:12,820 --> 00:14:16,259
Please pity this poor soul
and save him.

157
00:14:17,389 --> 00:14:19,529
Lord, we beg you.

158
00:14:21,429 --> 00:14:22,500
Please...

159
00:14:41,490 --> 00:14:44,460
We lost Dong Baek, sir.

160
00:14:45,120 --> 00:14:46,159
Get him.

161
00:14:48,429 --> 00:14:50,259
Bring all the men
from the Intelligence Agency.

162
00:14:51,830 --> 00:14:53,059
Yes, sir.

163
00:15:02,769 --> 00:15:05,080
- Where is he?
- He's one floor below, sir.

164
00:15:05,610 --> 00:15:06,840
Lead the way.

165
00:15:25,960 --> 00:15:27,500
Tell me who the Eraser is,

166
00:15:28,429 --> 00:15:29,799
and I'll spare you.

167
00:15:32,440 --> 00:15:36,409
I already died 20 years ago.

168
00:15:39,110 --> 00:15:40,980
It was the moment
I saw my brother's body...

169
00:15:42,879 --> 00:15:44,279
in the morgue.

170
00:15:49,690 --> 00:15:51,190
Oh, no...

171
00:15:52,220 --> 00:15:54,330
Yong Dae... No...

172
00:15:54,389 --> 00:15:55,759
No...

173
00:16:00,759 --> 00:16:02,269
No... No...

174
00:16:02,269 --> 00:16:03,500
This can't be...

175
00:16:03,830 --> 00:16:05,039
In his suicide note,

176
00:16:05,039 --> 00:16:06,899
he wrote that he couldn't bear
with the poverty.

177
00:16:07,340 --> 00:16:09,639
No, Yong Dae...

178
00:16:09,639 --> 00:16:12,409
Because of those words,
even my mom took her own life.

179
00:16:13,639 --> 00:16:15,279
Honey!

180
00:16:15,879 --> 00:16:17,980
- Stay with me!
- My dad couldn't bear it...

181
00:16:17,980 --> 00:16:19,220
and left home.

182
00:16:19,580 --> 00:16:21,090
His body...

183
00:16:21,990 --> 00:16:23,950
is probably underwater
somewhere in the mountains.

184
00:16:25,019 --> 00:16:26,960
And no one has probably found him.

185
00:16:28,759 --> 00:16:30,159
I knew...

186
00:16:30,860 --> 00:16:33,860
that the suicide note
was fabricated.

187
00:16:36,700 --> 00:16:38,500
If he had truly felt that way,

188
00:16:39,570 --> 00:16:42,370
he would've mentioned it in advance.

189
00:16:45,139 --> 00:16:47,279
Bang Jun Seok
only killed my brother.

190
00:16:47,809 --> 00:16:50,149
But you killed the rest of us.

191
00:16:50,179 --> 00:16:52,519
But what? You'll spare me?

192
00:16:52,750 --> 00:16:53,879
How?

193
00:16:54,850 --> 00:16:57,620
How's that possible when you already
killed me back then?

194
00:17:01,929 --> 00:17:03,590
Despite knowing everything,

195
00:17:04,700 --> 00:17:06,259
you still spared Bang Jun Seok?

196
00:17:06,329 --> 00:17:09,529
He doesn't deserve to die
that easily.

197
00:17:11,240 --> 00:17:13,299
The same goes for your son.

198
00:17:17,140 --> 00:17:19,410
- What?
- Do you think it was luck...

199
00:17:20,640 --> 00:17:21,849
that he survived?

200
00:17:23,079 --> 00:17:24,309
His pain...

201
00:17:25,720 --> 00:17:27,119
has just started.

202
00:17:35,759 --> 00:17:37,029
Who is the Eraser?

203
00:17:39,759 --> 00:17:40,759
I don't know.

204
00:17:42,769 --> 00:17:44,230
My memory has been erased.

205
00:17:55,009 --> 00:17:56,079
Fine.

206
00:17:57,410 --> 00:18:00,720
I guess you'll have to die, then.

207
00:18:02,049 --> 00:18:03,150
What are you going to do?

208
00:18:05,019 --> 00:18:06,460
Kill me yourself?

209
00:18:41,089 --> 00:18:43,730
I'd like to see him
for just a short while.

210
00:18:44,329 --> 00:18:45,630
I said, no.

211
00:18:46,059 --> 00:18:47,630
This isn't fair.

212
00:18:47,630 --> 00:18:49,470
I should be able to see him.

213
00:18:49,470 --> 00:18:51,269
I thought you two didn't have
anything going on.

214
00:19:06,019 --> 00:19:07,349
Where is the Eraser?

215
00:19:12,319 --> 00:19:13,759
Did you enjoy...

216
00:19:15,190 --> 00:19:18,029
watching your son burn to death?

217
00:19:20,430 --> 00:19:21,769
- What did you say?
- You know,

218
00:19:23,430 --> 00:19:24,539
my brother...

219
00:19:25,000 --> 00:19:27,369
was also burned
and pushed off a cliff.

220
00:19:27,470 --> 00:19:30,569
But the Eraser said
he's going to do it the other way.

221
00:19:31,640 --> 00:19:33,410
He'll make you fall first...

222
00:19:34,380 --> 00:19:36,750
and then slowly burn you to death.

223
00:19:38,150 --> 00:19:41,079
He said it'd be too boring
if you died too soon.

224
00:19:43,289 --> 00:19:44,289
Die.

225
00:19:48,359 --> 00:19:50,130
I wasn't going to tell you this,

226
00:19:50,559 --> 00:19:51,960
but he's a murder suspect.

227
00:19:54,200 --> 00:19:55,630
You should come here
with your lawyer.

228
00:19:55,630 --> 00:19:56,930
If not, you can't visit him.

229
00:20:01,440 --> 00:20:03,369
Why are you all out here?
Where's Moon Yong Gwang?

230
00:20:03,470 --> 00:20:05,380
The Intelligence Agency took over.

231
00:20:05,380 --> 00:20:08,380
- What?
- They have no right to do that.

232
00:20:10,910 --> 00:20:11,950
Chief Byun.

233
00:20:16,789 --> 00:20:17,849
It's been a while.

234
00:20:18,089 --> 00:20:20,289
Why is the chief of
the Intelligence Agency doing here?

235
00:20:20,819 --> 00:20:23,789
- Shall we have a chat?
- Let's talk another time.

236
00:20:24,329 --> 00:20:25,359
Secure the room.

237
00:20:25,359 --> 00:20:26,500
- Yes, sir.
- Yes, sir.

238
00:20:26,930 --> 00:20:28,369
This is the deputy chief's order.

239
00:20:30,329 --> 00:20:32,700
The deputy chief
and the director are upstairs.

240
00:20:32,700 --> 00:20:35,069
We'll pull out soon,
so please wait.

241
00:20:35,269 --> 00:20:36,309
They're interrogating.

242
00:20:36,470 --> 00:20:37,710
Who's interrogating?

243
00:20:39,779 --> 00:20:41,950
Section Chief Cheon Ki Soo
from the headquarters.

244
00:20:42,109 --> 00:20:43,309
Just act like you don't know.

245
00:20:44,619 --> 00:20:47,279
How could you let a family member
of a victim meet the suspect?

246
00:20:48,089 --> 00:20:51,119
You're one of Deputy Chief Lee's
men, aren't you?

247
00:20:54,789 --> 00:20:55,859
I'm not.

248
00:20:55,859 --> 00:20:57,430
All we have to do
is follow the orders.

249
00:20:57,690 --> 00:20:58,829
Secure the room!

250
00:20:58,829 --> 00:21:00,500
- Push through!
- Let's go!

251
00:21:00,829 --> 00:21:01,930
Stop them.

252
00:21:02,500 --> 00:21:04,130
- You can't go in.
- Push through.

253
00:21:04,640 --> 00:21:05,670
Hey.

254
00:21:11,910 --> 00:21:13,339
Who is the Eraser?

255
00:21:17,250 --> 00:21:20,250
With time,
you'll only feel more pain...

256
00:21:20,880 --> 00:21:22,349
from losing your son.

257
00:21:26,089 --> 00:21:27,589
Until your insides...

258
00:21:29,829 --> 00:21:31,859
get crushed into mush.

259
00:21:32,759 --> 00:21:35,769
You don't even need
to go into trial.

260
00:21:37,029 --> 00:21:38,500
You can just die in my hands.

261
00:21:51,619 --> 00:21:52,980
Move it!

262
00:21:55,019 --> 00:21:56,589
- Watch it.
- Move.

263
00:21:56,690 --> 00:21:58,920
- Hey, block him.
- Go.

264
00:21:58,920 --> 00:22:00,059
Byun Young Soo!

265
00:22:00,559 --> 00:22:02,059
(Moon Yong Gwang)

266
00:22:25,619 --> 00:22:27,920
You can go in first.

267
00:22:29,849 --> 00:22:30,920
It's cold.

268
00:22:38,430 --> 00:22:42,069
