Secondly,

514
00:36:28,320 --> 00:36:29,659
Assemblyman Bang...

515
00:36:30,590 --> 00:36:32,460
must get out of this...

516
00:36:34,130 --> 00:36:35,670
unscathed.

517
00:36:37,269 --> 00:36:39,000
You should turn this misfortune
into a blessing.

518
00:36:39,300 --> 00:36:42,469
Sympathy votes are the biggest asset
a politician can have.

519
00:36:42,469 --> 00:36:44,039
What would you know?

520
00:36:44,340 --> 00:36:45,409
Thirdly,

521
00:36:46,739 --> 00:36:50,309
the criminal who knows the secret
cannot walk into court.

522
00:36:50,780 --> 00:36:51,880
Never.

523
00:36:52,449 --> 00:36:53,750
I'll keep that in mind.

524
00:36:53,949 --> 00:36:55,150
Lastly,

525
00:36:56,219 --> 00:36:57,550
the scapegoat...

526
00:36:58,349 --> 00:37:00,090
will have to be buried as well.

527
00:37:03,130 --> 00:37:04,630
Are you talking about Dong Baek?

528
00:37:05,760 --> 00:37:08,230
Anyone who can become
a threat to my son...

529
00:37:08,400 --> 00:37:11,400
should all disappear.

530
00:37:15,199 --> 00:37:16,670
My wife can't get hurt.

531
00:37:17,909 --> 00:37:21,139
If anything goes wrong, you'll die.

532
00:37:25,980 --> 00:37:27,420
I'll do my best.

533
00:37:33,090 --> 00:37:34,619
Let me repeat myself.

534
00:37:34,920 --> 00:37:36,860
I don't care
if she makes it out alive.

535
00:37:39,130 --> 00:37:40,960
Actually, I want the opposite.

536
00:37:43,369 --> 00:37:44,429
Keep that in mind.

537
00:37:46,369 --> 00:37:48,139
I have a different stance from you,

538
00:37:49,369 --> 00:37:50,610
but we have the same goal.

539
00:37:53,179 --> 00:37:55,679
Getting rid of the Eraser
and Dong Baek at once...

540
00:37:56,510 --> 00:37:58,250
is the only way...

541
00:37:59,050 --> 00:38:00,480
to protect our children.

542
00:38:16,500 --> 00:38:17,599
Meadow!

543
00:38:50,230 --> 00:38:52,739
Why did you eat it all?

544
00:38:52,940 --> 00:38:54,099
What?

545
00:38:56,710 --> 00:38:57,739
You shouldn't...

546
00:39:42,619 --> 00:39:43,849
Are you going out for a walk
at this hour?

547
00:39:46,690 --> 00:39:48,860
Did you stay up all night
so you could watch me?

548
00:39:50,230 --> 00:39:52,500
- I sleep lightly.
- Just act like you didn't see me.

549
00:39:53,099 --> 00:39:55,030
Those who are pressured by guilt...

550
00:39:55,030 --> 00:39:57,130
often throw themselves
into danger and death.

551
00:39:58,329 --> 00:40:00,599
- No one's dying.
- It's not Meadow.

552
00:40:01,599 --> 00:40:04,110
The child in Eun Soo Gyeong
isn't Seol Meadow.

553
00:40:04,110 --> 00:40:05,739
- This isn't about that.
- Yes, it is.

554
00:40:06,110 --> 00:40:07,980
You haven't rid yourself
of the guilt from seven years ago.

555
00:40:07,980 --> 00:40:10,380
I'm just trying to stop him from
making her suffer because of me.

556
00:40:10,380 --> 00:40:12,010
How is that because of you?

557
00:40:12,409 --> 00:40:13,480
He's playing mind games.

558
00:40:13,619 --> 00:40:15,519
- I'll be back.
- You could really die.

559
00:40:15,519 --> 00:40:16,519
It doesn't matter.

560
00:40:16,519 --> 00:40:18,320
What I hate more is someone else
getting hurt because of me.

561
00:40:21,860 --> 00:40:23,489
What... What? What is this?

562
00:40:24,130 --> 00:40:25,190
What's going on?

563
00:40:25,460 --> 00:40:27,059
Baek, seriously.

564
00:40:27,460 --> 00:40:29,800
For goodness' sake, I knew it.

565
00:40:30,369 --> 00:40:32,869
I told you. It was a good idea
to install an alarm.

566
00:40:33,199 --> 00:40:35,170
Handcuff him so
he won't go anywhere.

567
00:40:35,269 --> 00:40:36,510
You've all done enough.

568
00:40:37,469 --> 00:40:39,070
- It's my fight now.
- Cut the nonsense.

569
00:40:39,380 --> 00:40:42,110
Who do you think you are,
a superhuman or something?

570
00:40:42,409 --> 00:40:43,550
Stay out of this, Old Man.

571
00:40:43,550 --> 00:40:44,750
You have to see your kid
getting married.

572
00:40:44,750 --> 00:40:46,150
Shut your mouth.

573
00:40:46,150 --> 00:40:48,380
Wherever it may be,
we'll always be with you.

574
00:40:48,380 --> 00:40:50,619
As long as you don't stress me out
and listen to me,

575
00:40:50,619 --> 00:40:52,519
I'll be able to live until I'm 100.

576
00:40:53,889 --> 00:40:55,360
Se Hoon, you should
stay out of this too.

577
00:40:55,559 --> 00:40:56,690
You're making me upset.

578
00:40:57,159 --> 00:40:59,260
Robin should always
be beside Batman.

579
00:40:59,630 --> 00:41:00,730
What about me then?

580
00:41:02,030 --> 00:41:03,269
Alfred?

581
00:41:03,269 --> 00:41:04,929
Alfred? Isn't that their dog's name?

582
00:41:05,500 --> 00:41:07,300
He's the butler that manages
the house.

583
00:41:07,539 --> 00:41:08,570
You're perfect for the role.

584
00:41:12,469 --> 00:41:13,539
We're on the same team.

585
00:41:15,639 --> 00:41:17,880
Let's just follow Dong Baek around.
I'll be the director.

586
00:41:17,949 --> 00:41:19,550
Senior Superintendent Han
is the one in charge.

587
00:41:19,550 --> 00:41:21,750
She's our captain.

588
00:41:21,880 --> 00:41:24,650
Captain, aren't you hungry?
You're wide awake, right?

589
00:41:24,650 --> 00:41:26,420
It's still in
the middle of the night.

590
00:41:26,420 --> 00:41:29,230
Why are you wandering about
in the morning? My goodness.

591
00:41:29,230 --> 00:41:32,190
You really know how to annoy me.
I just want to smack you sometimes.

592
00:41:32,860 --> 00:41:34,059
How about some ramyeon?

593
00:41:34,230 --> 00:41:35,800
Captain, do you eat ramyeon?

594
00:41:36,070 --> 00:41:37,570
- Sounds good.
- Okay.

595
00:41:37,570 --> 00:41:38,900
Who's buying?
Rock-paper-scissors.

596
00:41:39,099 --> 00:41:40,699
- I won. You go.
- Go get ramyeon.

597
00:41:57,789 --> 00:42:00,519
Joon! My son.

598
00:42:03,929 --> 00:42:05,690
- Dad.
- Yes, it's me.

599
00:42:06,699 --> 00:42:09,130
- Can you recognize me?
- Yes.

600
00:42:09,230 --> 00:42:10,369
He has passed the critical stage.

601
00:42:11,570 --> 00:42:12,940
Let's focus on his recovery now.

602
00:42:14,269 --> 00:42:15,500
Thank you.

603
00:42:15,500 --> 00:42:16,909
Thank you, sir.

604
00:42:18,710 --> 00:42:19,809
Honey.

605
00:42:21,409 --> 00:42:22,510
Thank you.

606
00:42:22,909 --> 00:42:24,010
My son.

607
00:43:04,519 --> 00:43:06,019
How is your son?

608
00:43:10,960 --> 00:43:12,090
He has passed the critical stage.

609
00:43:14,130 --> 00:43:15,199
He's in a critical condition.

610
00:43:16,730 --> 00:43:19,940
Where did it all start going wrong?

611
00:43:21,969 --> 00:43:23,139
Do you blame me?

612
00:43:26,110 --> 00:43:27,409
You were my savior...

613
00:43:28,809 --> 00:43:29,949
until a few days ago.

614
00:43:31,750 --> 00:43:35,750
I was about to be fired,
but you made me into a chief.

615
00:43:37,050 --> 00:43:39,360
- And now?
- It's meaningless.

616
00:43:41,360 --> 00:43:42,789
Since my son died.

617
00:43:48,659 --> 00:43:49,800
Get some rest.

618
00:43:50,829 --> 00:43:52,369
I'll make sure you get your revenge.

619
00:43:54,369 --> 00:43:55,570
Who is the Eraser?

620
00:43:58,639 --> 00:44:00,539
- It's not your business.
- It is!

621
00:44:02,010 --> 00:44:03,250
Consider it the price of
my son's life.

622
00:44:13,519 --> 00:44:14,590
Dong Baek.

623
00:44:20,400 --> 00:44:21,530
Are you sure?

624
00:44:28,199 --> 00:44:29,340
He's an accomplice
at the very least.

625
00:44:31,170 --> 00:44:32,409
This is a video
taken at the safe house.

626
00:44:32,940 --> 00:44:34,179
In that backpack...

627
00:44:35,039 --> 00:44:37,909
is the weapon he used
to do that to my son.

628
00:44:55,130 --> 00:44:58,329
He's after Chairwoman Hwang.

629
00:45:38,170 --> 00:45:39,480
That's RIU's undercover vehicle.

630
00:45:48,920 --> 00:45:50,550
The Intelligence Agency
is staking out too.

631
00:45:51,849 --> 00:45:54,289
- What do we do?
- What do you think? Let's just go.

632
00:45:54,489 --> 00:45:55,519
No.

633
00:45:55,519 --> 00:45:57,230
No? How are we going to
get past them?

634
00:46:08,440 --> 00:46:10,239
(Viewer Ratings)

635
00:46:10,909 --> 00:46:13,309
Goodness, look at these ratings.

636
00:46:15,380 --> 00:46:19,409
But what if the Eraser tips-off
another media outlet next time?

637
00:46:19,409 --> 00:46:20,519
It can't be helped.

638
00:46:20,780 --> 00:46:23,219
It's better than wasting time
and blowing a scoop.

639
00:46:25,190 --> 00:46:27,360
Make sure to take care of
Kang Ji Eun.

640
00:46:28,389 --> 00:46:29,460
Yes, sir.

641
00:46:30,889 --> 00:46:31,989
Yes, sir.

642
00:46:39,639 --> 00:46:41,800
Hey, what are you doing?

643
00:46:42,039 --> 00:46:43,309
Hey, wait!

644
00:46:46,309 --> 00:46:48,909
From now on, you can wait in here.

645
00:47:04,130 --> 00:47:05,130
What about my laptop?

646
00:47:05,130 --> 00:47:07,099
We have the right to confiscate
all company property.

647
00:47:07,760 --> 00:47:08,829
When you need to go somewhere,

648
00:47:08,829 --> 00:47:10,699
receive prior permission
from the Administrative Team.

649
00:47:11,230 --> 00:47:12,300
Even when you have to use
the restroom.

650
00:47:12,300 --> 00:47:15,070
If you don't, you'll receive
additional disciplinary action.

651
00:47:29,449 --> 00:47:32,420
(Restricted Number)

652
00:47:33,789 --> 00:47:34,860
Yes?

653
00:47:37,190 --> 00:47:38,260
What?

654
00:47:40,059 --> 00:47:42,159
Former assemblyman Bang Jun Seok...

655
00:47:42,159 --> 00:47:44,269
will make
a public announcement shortly.

656
00:47:44,429 --> 00:47:47,969
We expect him to send a message
to the perp who abducted his wife.

657
00:47:48,139 --> 00:47:51,969
While he embraced the socially weak
with his strong leadership,

658
00:47:52,239 --> 00:47:56,380
he was a man of conviction
who fought against justice.

659
00:47:56,510 --> 00:48:00,019
There are also opinions he will
respond according to his principles.

660
00:48:12,929 --> 00:48:14,130
Did you memorize the script?

661
00:48:16,329 --> 00:48:18,670
Everything will go well
if I follow that script?

662
00:48:19,469 --> 00:48:22,000
No, Soo Gyeong won't come back.

663
00:48:23,110 --> 00:48:24,139
Mom.

664
00:48:25,070 --> 00:48:28,010
Do you think her abductors
wouldn't have told her anything?

665
00:48:28,239 --> 00:48:29,750
But still, how could we
abandon Soo Gyeong?

666
00:48:29,750 --> 00:48:32,809
No. It's Soo Gyeong
who will abandon you.

667
00:48:34,019 --> 00:48:37,489
If she returns safely,
will she still be on your side?

668
00:48:37,820 --> 00:48:38,989
With her personality?

669
00:48:41,460 --> 00:48:43,389
Determining who is on your side
is simple.

670
00:48:44,389 --> 00:48:46,800
Someone who never thinks
of betraying you...

671
00:48:46,800 --> 00:48:48,929
even when they know
every dirty little secret about you.

672
00:48:51,130 --> 00:48:55,900
It's rather someone like her who
maybe on your side until the end.

673
00:48:59,940 --> 00:49:01,280
But, still.

674
00:49:12,989 --> 00:49:14,460
I guess you're not.

675
00:49:20,929 --> 00:49:22,699
You're someone who will betray him.

676
00:49:24,670 --> 00:49:26,230
- No, ma'am...
- Mr. Cho.

677
00:49:35,639 --> 00:49:37,610
This is what you call
someone on your side.

678
00:49:38,110 --> 00:49:41,449
Someone who can kill without
hesitation upon your order.

679
00:49:53,260 --> 00:49:54,900
I don't like her eyes.

680
00:49:59,739 --> 00:50:01,300
Still, how can I abandon Soo Gyeong?

681
00:50:01,300 --> 00:50:02,869
I said she will abandon you!

682
00:50:02,869 --> 00:50:04,539
Still, I should persuade her.

683
00:50:05,440 --> 00:50:06,880
She's even pregnant with my child.

684
00:50:07,139 --> 00:50:08,340
Son.

685
00:50:09,239 --> 00:50:10,909
Don't be afraid of losing things.

686
00:50:10,949 --> 00:50:14,519
What you should be afraid of
is not being able to have more.

687
00:50:15,719 --> 00:50:17,849
You will lose more things
from now on.

688
00:50:18,090 --> 00:50:20,719
You'll have no choice but to
share your power...

689
00:50:20,719 --> 00:50:22,420
to people all around you.

690
00:50:23,630 --> 00:50:26,630
But keep this in mind.

691
00:50:28,030 --> 00:50:29,599
When you lose something,

692
00:50:29,659 --> 00:50:32,929
think about how much more
you'll be able to gain.

693
00:50:34,800 --> 00:50:36,469
If Soo Gyeong dies,

694
00:50:37,710 --> 00:50:40,539
it will become a successful
investment that gifts you...

695
00:50:40,539 --> 00:50:42,079
with the biggest winning ever.

696
00:50:45,710 --> 00:50:46,820
Do you understand?

697
00:50:52,719 --> 00:50:54,820
- Let's go.
- Which way is it?

698
00:50:54,820 --> 00:50:56,889
- We need to hurry.
- Come on.

699
00:50:57,030 --> 00:50:58,489
- Hurry.
- This way.

700
00:50:58,690 --> 00:50:59,900
Come on.

701
00:51:01,530 --> 00:51:03,530
- Over there!
- What's going on?

702
00:51:21,750 --> 00:51:23,550
Dong Baek is headed up
towards our trap.

703
00:51:47,110 --> 00:51:49,239
(Tae Cheol Logistics)

704
00:51:55,550 --> 00:51:57,789
- You must not shoot him.
- Professor Han.

705
00:51:59,860 --> 00:52:01,590
The Eraser will go after
Chairwoman Hwang.

706
00:52:02,119 --> 00:52:04,030
- We'll capture him alive.
- Kill him.

707
00:52:04,190 --> 00:52:06,800
If Dong Baek is the Eraser,
we shouldn't kill him.

708
00:52:07,230 --> 00:52:08,329
How will you handle the backlash?

709
00:52:08,329 --> 00:52:09,659
The higher-ups
will take responsibility.

710
00:52:10,030 --> 00:52:11,500
There's no proof he is the Eraser.

711
00:52:11,530 --> 00:52:13,340
The one who goes after
Chairwoman Hwang is the Eraser.

712
00:52:13,699 --> 00:52:14,699
Do you have proof?

713
00:52:14,699 --> 00:52:16,570
My words are the proof!

714
00:52:22,909 --> 00:52:24,949
You placed that truck
where it stands out, didn't you?

715
00:52:25,050 --> 00:52:27,519
You knew Det. Dong was innocent,
and you were warning him.

716
00:52:29,079 --> 00:52:31,050
(Former Assemblyman Bang Jun Seok's
Press Conference)

717
00:52:50,469 --> 00:52:51,639
To the people of our nation,

718
00:52:52,469 --> 00:52:53,510
please...

719
00:52:54,409 --> 00:52:56,510
forgive me for standing
in this position today...

720
00:52:58,449 --> 00:53:01,550
because of my personal issue.

721
00:53:02,820 --> 00:53:06,489
For the last 12 years
as an assemblyman,

722
00:53:06,989 --> 00:53:09,860
I have never bent my principles
for my personal profit.

723
00:53:10,360 --> 00:53:11,760
Not once.

724
00:53:12,829 --> 00:53:16,230
However, I have no choice but to...

725
00:53:18,300 --> 00:53:19,940
cast aside my principles today.

726
00:53:23,670 --> 00:53:25,510
I'd like to plead to the person
who abducted my wife.

727
00:53:26,539 --> 00:53:29,679
Please do not hurt...

728
00:53:30,349 --> 00:53:31,750
my innocent wife.

729
00:53:33,150 --> 00:53:35,019
Whatever grudge you have
against Det. Dong,

730
00:53:37,219 --> 00:53:38,449
I am willing to...

731
00:53:41,260 --> 00:53:42,659
suffer in his place.

732
00:53:59,139 --> 00:54:00,179
Give him a chance.

733
00:54:00,710 --> 00:54:02,739
A chance for Det. Dong
to find the smoking gun.

734
00:54:02,739 --> 00:54:04,010
I already gave the order.

735
00:54:04,150 --> 00:54:05,150
Chief.

736
00:54:13,820 --> 00:54:16,559
Not to shoot, no matter who it is.

737
00:54:24,869 --> 00:54:26,130
What are you doing here?

738
00:54:27,400 --> 00:54:28,469
Beats me.

739
00:54:35,210 --> 00:54:37,949
I plead once again to the person
who has my wife.

740
00:54:38,280 --> 00:54:40,679
Whether I step down from my position
or donate all my money,

741
00:54:41,050 --> 00:54:42,079
I'll do anything you want.

742
00:54:43,050 --> 00:54:45,420
If you want to kill someone,
I will die 100, no 1,000 times...

743
00:54:46,550 --> 00:54:47,860
instead of her.

744
00:54:49,690 --> 00:54:51,230
If I can save my wife,

745
00:54:53,059 --> 00:54:54,659
I will give up everything...

746
00:54:55,829 --> 00:54:57,230
and get on my knees to beg.

747
00:55:32,500 --> 00:55:33,840
It's Det. Dong.

748
00:55:33,840 --> 00:55:35,400
- It really is.
- What is he doing?

749
00:55:35,570 --> 00:55:36,710
It's Det. Dong.

750
00:55:54,590 --> 00:55:57,030
- Are you getting this?
- What is he doing?

751
00:55:57,090 --> 00:55:58,929
- He has a gun!
- What?

752
00:55:58,960 --> 00:56:02,199
- Hey, he has a gun!
- Keep shooting!

753
00:56:41,940 --> 00:56:43,510
- Put down the gun.
- Put it down!

754
00:56:43,510 --> 00:56:44,570
- Put it down now!
- Put it down!

755
00:56:44,570 --> 00:56:46,269
- Put it down!
- Watch out!

756
00:56:48,239 --> 00:56:49,579
Are you okay?

757
00:56:54,449 --> 00:56:56,519
- Grab him!
- Watch out.

758
00:56:56,519 --> 00:56:58,750
- Catch him.
- Put the gun down!

759
00:56:58,750 --> 00:56:59,820
Put it down!

760
00:57:16,969 --> 00:57:18,739
- Put down the gun.
- Put it down!

761
00:57:18,739 --> 00:57:20,239
- Put it down.
- Don't come near me.

762
00:57:20,239 --> 00:57:21,780
- Stop!
- Wait.

763
00:57:21,780 --> 00:57:23,710
- He's running away!
- Put it down!

764
00:57:24,050 --> 00:57:25,610
- Catch him!
- Stop!

765
00:57:26,480 --> 00:57:28,150
- Go after him!
- Grab him!

766
00:57:30,119 --> 00:57:31,320
Hey!

767
00:57:32,989 --> 00:57:34,320
Go after him!

768
00:57:39,329 --> 00:57:41,000
- Which way did he go?
- Hurry!

769
00:57:57,949 --> 00:57:59,010
It's a tear gas gun.

770
00:58:01,119 --> 00:58:02,219
Wait.

771
00:58:07,760 --> 00:58:09,789
Let's go. This way.

772
00:58:09,789 --> 00:58:12,190
- It's all right.
- Find him!

773
00:58:12,460 --> 00:58:14,159
- Where did he go?
- This way!

774
00:58:14,260 --> 00:58:15,400
Take him and get out of here.

775
00:58:17,170 --> 00:58:18,500
He went that way!

776
00:58:32,050 --> 00:58:33,250
I'll go get the car.

777
00:58:47,500 --> 00:58:49,630
(Detective Dong Baek)

778
00:58:51,230 --> 00:58:53,769
(Detective Dong Baek)

779
00:58:54,739 --> 00:58:55,769
Go ahead.

780
00:58:55,840 --> 00:58:57,340
The day Moon Yong Dae died,

781
00:58:58,510 --> 00:59:01,480
there was another victim.

782
00:59:03,409 --> 00:59:05,349
She died from being raped.

783
00:59:06,610 --> 00:59:09,920
Yoo Ah Yeong, age 20.

784
00:59:11,219 --> 00:59:12,750
Her dad...

785
00:59:14,389 --> 00:59:15,820
is the head of the fire department.

786
00:59:17,329 --> 00:59:18,530
Shimbae Fire Station.

787
00:59:18,760 --> 00:59:20,900
We have VIP guests.
What are you doing?

788
00:59:20,900 --> 00:59:22,300
Hurry and prepare
a welcoming ceremony.

789
00:59:22,860 --> 00:59:24,070
It's him.

790
00:59:24,929 --> 00:59:26,099
The Eraser.

791
00:59:27,769 --> 00:59:31,110
Today at the WI Building,
former assemblyman Bang Jun Seok...

792
00:59:31,110 --> 00:59:34,210
held a press conference regarding
the abduction of Eun Soo Gyeong.

793
00:59:34,579 --> 00:59:37,679
Assemblyman Bang pleaded for him
to spare his wife...

794
00:59:37,679 --> 00:59:40,820
when Det. Dong suddenly appeared
and caused a commotion.

795
00:59:41,920 --> 00:59:43,920
- Send a team to his home now.
- Yes, ma'am.

796
01:01:34,130 --> 01:01:37,000
That day, two kids were killed.

797
01:01:37,170 --> 01:01:38,469
Please don't kill me.

798
01:01:38,900 --> 01:01:39,929
You need to stay alert.

799
01:01:40,070 --> 01:01:42,469
You have too many enemies
around you right now.

800
01:01:42,739 --> 01:01:44,670
Det. Dong is not a criminal yet.

801
01:01:44,940 --> 01:01:46,070
We'll see about that.

802
01:01:46,210 --> 01:01:47,679
We've confirmed the identity
of the culprit,

803
01:01:47,739 --> 01:01:49,179
so he will be killed soon.

804
01:01:49,380 --> 01:01:52,480
If something goes down today,
you can really scan...

805
01:01:52,579 --> 01:01:53,610
all of my memories.

806
01:01:53,750 --> 01:01:55,480
I want to testify.

807
01:01:55,579 --> 01:01:58,349
The most important thing
for a reporter is the truth.

808
01:01:58,590 --> 01:02:00,760
Will I really be able to change?
